-- Author Harper Sees Worst Job Market for Law Students (Audio)
-- B y
-- 2013-07-05T12:00:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-05/author-harper-sees-worst-job-market-for-law-students-audio-.html
Steven Harper, a recently retired 
partner of Chicago-based Kirkland & Ellis LLP and author of "The
Lawyer Bubble: A Profession in Crisis," says only half of 
graduating law school students will have get jobs. Harper talks 
with Bloomberg's  Tom Keene  and Scarlet Fu on Bloomberg Radio's 
"Bloomberg Surveillance."   
 (Source: Bloomberg)  Running time 04:34
 